# Flask Project Rules

Always follow Flask best practices.

- Use Blueprint architecture.
- Keep routes modular.
- Separate models, routes, and templates.
- Use Flask-SQLAlchemy for database access.
- Use Flask-Login for authentication.
- Use clean Jinja templates.
- Use reusable components.
- Keep CSS in the static folder.
- Never break existing routes.
- Maintain a healthcare project production structure.
- Follow secure coding practices for patient data.
